LA Restore
Louisiana Restore (LA Restore) is a state-funded grant program created to help homeowners recover from natural disasters ‚Äî including Hurricane Francine and Hurricane Ida.
These grants are designed to cover essential repairs, replacement housing, and rebuilding needs for families impacted by storm damage.
At Gulf South Homes, we make the process simple and stress-free.
If you‚Äôve been approved for an LA Restore grant, we accept all grant types, and we work directly with you to make sure your funds are applied correctly toward your new manufactured or modular home.

What We Do for LA Restore Customers
Help you select an eligible home
Provide the paperwork required by LA Restore
Work with your case manager
Ensure your home meets grant program guidelines
Coordinate delivery, setup, and required inspections

We Accept Every LA Restore Grant

Whether your grant covers full replacement, partial replacement, or repair-related funding ‚Äî we accept ALL of it.

You bring the approval.
We handle the rest.

